Sally Horsfall Eaton served as the first Chancellor of George Brown College from an unspecified year onwards. She presided over convocation ceremonies and served as an ambassador for the college, enhancing its profile in the community. During her tenure, she ushered in new traditions for convocation, including George Brown College’s ceremonial mace and coat of arms. The Nursing School at George Brown College was renamed in Sally Horsfall Eaton's honour following a $4-million gift given by her and her husband, John C. Eaton. Horsfall Eaton has a long and distinguished record of volunteerism, philanthropy and public service.
